column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Shield Piercing -  Missiles ignore shields. Use missiles to damage a powerful ship's Shields System. Just remember that Defense Drones can shoot down missiles!
Your jump leads to a completely unremarkable binary star system. There is nothing else around.

It appears the slaves did not survive the fighting. You find their burnt bodies in the hold, but before you strip the ship you hear faint noises in the walls. You break off a latch and a slave falls out of a hidden compartment, coughing. Once recomposed the slave offers to join your crew.
The colonists hand over the supplies and you load it onto your ship. As you jump away, you crack it open and discover nothing more than vaccinations for a local plague.
It seems the crew did not survive the assault. You take what you can from the remains of the ship.
Scans reveal a number of asteroids with useful compositions. You extract some fuel.
You decide you need what supplies you have.
A transmission from the nearby planet indicates an outpost below which offers supplies to travelers. You send down an away party to check it out.
column12: Weapon: LASER HEAVY 1, BOMB 1, LASER BURST 5, System: drones, medbay, sensors, Drone: REPAIR, COMBAT 1, DEFENSE 1,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You approach cautiously but you detect no danger. It appears to have been a small rest stop that was abandoned a while ago. You take what few supplies you can find.
Welcome to a new sector! Get to the exit beacon and jump to the next sector before the pursuing Rebels catch you!
The station was either abandoned or stripped clean. It seems to have lain unused for quite some time. You find nothing useful.
Thank you! If you can just give us a count on their numbers perhaps we can get the Rebels to help. Added a quest marker to your map!
A ship engineer has set up a small shop here.
column12: System: sensors, mind, hacking, Crew: Mantis, Mantis, Rock, Augment: FTL JUMPER, FLEET DISTRACTION, BATTERY BOOSTER,

column11: With the patrol ship destroyed you hasten to leave. It won't be long before the other ships catch up.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

With no fear of catching the disease, your Engi crewmember helps reassure and organize the infected humans. Calmed by its extensive knowledge of human physiology, the infected submit to the quarantine in the hopes that a cure can be found soon. The colony leaders offer a reward for helping to prevent an ugly incident.
You thank them but prepare to move on.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.
column12: Weapon: BEAM 3, LASER HEAVY 1, BOMB STUN, Drone: COMBAT 2, COMBAT 1, REPAIR, System: drones, cloaking, clonebay, Crew: Mantis, Mantis, Human,

column11: With the crew dead, you are able to take the fuel out of storage. You also take all the scrap you can manage.
Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There is a small planet nearby with scattered settlements. A small Rebel fleet is in orbit with many ships ferrying back and forth. It must be a more recently 'liberated' planet.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The scout jumps away. They are sure to have informed the fleet of your position. You must get to the next Sector as soon as possible!

They reluctantly agree. Once aboard, you watch as their ship crashes against a massive rock. They thank you, but say I don't know what we'll do without our ship. As the Captain, I feel obligated to help you with your mission.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You discover a re-supply station used by Rebels and civilians alike. You transmit your fake ship identification and for once, they don't seem to recognize your ship. You try to assume the air of a local as you prepare to dock.
column12: Crew: Human, Rock, Mantis, Augment: FIRE EXTINGUISHERS, FTL JAMMER, WEAPON PREIGNITE, Weapon: ION 2, SHOTGUN, ION STUN,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

The refugee ship claims pirates have been following their trail since they left their homeworld. As a gesture of good will (and seeing how effectively you dispatched the enemy ship), they offer up what supplies they can spare.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
They transmit the space dock's coordinates. Added a quest marker to your map!
Their ship goes silent and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.

They reluctantly agree. Once aboard, you watch as their ship crashes against a massive rock. They thank you, but say I don't know what we'll do without our ship. As the Captain, I feel obligated to help you with your mission.
The outpost hails you, Thank you! I don't know what we did to anger the Rebels, but they were ready to kill us. I'll show you our goods and patch up your hull.
column12: Weapon: LASER BURST 2 A, BOMB 1, BOMB BREACH 2, System: drones, mind, hacking,

column11: Your crew calmly lines up for the Zoltans to take their readings. After a short time, the process is done. They contact you, Thank you for your participation in our study. Please accept these small cakes made from stiff dough as well as some scrap.
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.
column12: Weapon: BOMB ION, BOMB STUN, LASER HEAVY 2, Augment: DEFENSE SCRAMBLER, FTL BOOSTER, EXPLOSIVE REPLICATOR,

column11: This nebula must have been an important hub at one point; placing all of these jump beacons would be no easy task. However, now it's hardly navigable.
An abandoned space station circles a lonely planet. A quick check yields schematics for a drone. You bring it aboard the ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.
column12: System: drones, sensors, battery, Drone: ANTI DRONE, DEFENSE 2, COMBAT 2, Weapon: LASER CHARGEGUN, LASER HEAVY 1, BEAM FIRE, Augment: TELEPORT HEAL, O2 MASKS, ZOLTAN BYPASS,

column11: With the crew dead, you are able to take the fuel out of storage. You also take all the scrap you can manage.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
You beam the Federation crew aboard. One gladly joins your crew, the rest wait to be dropped off at the next station.
There's nothing here, save for vast swirls of gas reflecting rays from a distant sun.
Searching the remains you find that the cargo was military-grade Drone Schematics! You bring them aboard to install on your ship.
You cycle through wide-band comm channels as soon as you arrive. Nothing but static.

You discover a cluster of Federation refugee ships taking shelter in the folds of the nebula. I'm sorry we've got nothing to give you, but we need scrap to keep the engines running. You sense they'll strike a trade.
column12: System: drones, sensors, cloaking, Augment: WEAPON PREIGNITE, FTL JAMMER, ADV SCANNERS, Crew: Human, Zoltan, Human, Drone: ANTI DRONE, DEFENSE 2, DRONE SHIELD,

column11: The ship is completely abandoned. It looks like it ran out of fuel... and the crew ran out of food not long after. Despite the grisly scene that remains, you are able to scavenge some supplies from the cargo hold.
The Rock grudgingly transfer control of their helm to you and you steer them to a thinner part of the nebula. They're not sure what to think, but transfer over some supplies all the same.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
You've entered Zoltan territory. This species is not renowned for giving anything for nothing, but you can always be assured a fair hearing.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You bring the ship closer. The Slug enters a trance-like state for 1 to 2 seconds, then quickly snaps out of it. He states, This person is clearly unstable. It is best we leave them alone.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You beam the Federation crew aboard. One gladly joins your crew, the rest wait to be dropped off at the next station.
With the crew dead, you are able to take the fuel out of storage. You also take all the scrap you can manage.
You find a weapon system on their ship. With no crew to stop you, you can install it on your own.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?
column12: Drone: COMBAT 1, COMBAT FIRE, COMBAT BEAM, System: drones, battery, mind, Augment: ZOLTAN BYPASS, LIFE SCANNER, CLOAK FIRE,

column11: A Mantis crew here has hunkered down in the abdomen of a long-dead space-whale - the only way, presumably, for them to operate their black-market trade without detection. Worth a look?
column12: System: drones, cloaking, battery, Augment: DEFENSE SCRAMBLER, CLOAK FIRE, BATTERY BOOSTER, Drone: ANTI DRONE, BOARDER ION, COMBAT BEAM,

column11: There appear to be a number of small stations nearby. Before you have time to scan them, warnings go off. A Rebel teleporter was used in one of the stations. You've been boarded!

They finish: Please, spread the word of enlightenment to those that have not heard. Once you have, contact our brethren. They transmit coordinates of their so-called brethren. Added a quest marker to the next sector!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
This ship's cargo was not salvageable. However, they seem to have been surveying the region; they possess detailed maps and data. You download what you can to the ship's map.
The Rock people are a powerful and proud race. It is not unheard of to have a peaceful journey through their lands, but don't count on it.
Great. Take this bit of fuel as a down-payment. We'll be one step behind you, following your jump signatures. Don't want to take any risks now, do we? Added a quest marker to your map!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You arrive and the ship you were escorting jumps in behind you. Thanks for the help. We work at a nearby fusion power plant, we could try to improve your reactor's output as a form of compensation.
A few freighters pass by but they refuse all communications. Must not want to sully their reputation by talking with foreigners.

Although your methods are crude and most certainly ineffective, it is clear you took our previous meeting to heart. If your ship represents the Federation's willingness to adapt we shall do what we can to aid in their fight. This technology should aid your quest.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Your crew grabs what they can and returns to the ship before the asteroid hits. You take a look at what you've recovered once you move clear of the asteroid field.

Tully responds, It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck.
There is a a mobile ship construction platform stationed at this beacon. After a brief exchange they give you clearance to receive emergency repairs and military supplies.

You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
An Engi civilian ship-yard has been converted into a military refueling station. They offer you the chance to patch up your ship and refresh some supplies.
